  "prompt": "How much money per hour do Uber drivers make in Des Moines? What's the most a person can reasonably make per month?",
  "response": "As of my last update, Uber drivers in Des Moines, Iowa, can typically expect to earn between $15 to $25 per hour after expenses, but this can vary based on factors such as demand, time of day, and ride volume. \n\nOn average, if you assume a driver works around 20 to 25 hours a week, this could translate to a monthly income of approximately $1,200 to $2,500 before taxes and any other deductions. However, more active drivers, especially during peak times or special events, might be able to make more, possibly reaching up to $3,000 to $4,000 monthly, again depending on hours worked and expenses incurred.\n\nKeep in mind that these figures are subject to change due to factors such as Uber's pay structure and local economic conditions, so it's a good idea to check for the most current data or reviews from drivers in the area.",
